1018—1020. The words between brackets are considered by Wagner and others to be an interpolation. Madvig however argues that if they had been introduced by any one, he would at least have written a complete verse; that they are to the point and present no sign of interpolation. He thinks that some words have been lost and that they originally stood in somewhat this way :

Sed quum mayis credundum siet indidem esse oriundum id, quod est consimile moribus, convinces etc.
